# Session 06 — Local distance-based scaling estimator (feasibility test)

## Context

R1-revised emits minimal `(R, t)` on every benchmark subject but
cannot recover per-axis scale via density-map NCC
(`sessions/05_R1_revised/log.md` §Deviation 2). This session tests a
different signal: **estimate `sxy` and `sz` from local ROI-to-ROI
distance statistics (or local volume density)** — CZ GCaMP+ centroids
vs HCR GFP+ centroids localized inside HCR via R1.

Scope: **estimate `(sxy, sz)` only, verify against the known
anisotropic expansion table in `code/docs/01 Data Description.md`
(sxy ∈ 1.64–1.92, sz ∈ 2.13–3.58).** No R1 wiring in this session.
If the estimator clears the stopping bar (all 6 subjects within
± 20 %), it becomes the candidate scale source for the continued R1
effort in a follow-up session.

